hnology is available; whether a sound business case can be made for the deployment; and asks why, given this, the industry appears so supportive of 5G. He then puts forth the argument in favor of consistent connectivity of around 10Mbits/s everywhere as a more compelling vision and shows how it can be delivered via a mix of 4G and Wi-Fi.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Dez 2018) 4a5G. 4aCellular. 4aHigh speed internet. 4aInternet of things. 4aNetworking standard. 4aNetworking. 4aWireless technology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2018z9783110603118oZDB-23-DEI0 cEPUBz97815474012080 cprintz978154741728540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781547401185423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781547401185.jpg  aPDA5EBK  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DEIb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aPDA14ALL  aPDA1ALL